modules.description: Provides type definitions and interface specifications for implementing network protocols in MirageOS, including Ethernet, ARP, IP, ICMP, UDP, and TCP for both IPv4 and IPv6. Works with protocol-specific data structures such as packet headers, addresses, and socket interfaces. Used to ensure consistent protocol handling across network stack implementations in unikernel environments.

Provides functions to handle IP packet input, output, and error formatting, with support for TCP, UDP, and custom protocols. Operates on IP addresses, buffers, and callbacks for packet demultiplexing and transmission. Used to manage IPv4 communication, including sending fragmented packets, calculating checksums, and retrieving interface IP addresses.
